commText: Kohli and du Plessis are at the crease. Kohli is on strike. Chahar will open the attack
Chahar to Kohli, wide, plenty of movement!! A bit of extra bounce and away movement from outside off, takes the ball too wide
Chahar to Kohli, 1 run, on a length and nibbles inwards slightly towards off stump, Kohli squeezes it towards deep backward point to get to the other end
Chahar to du Plessis, no run, fuller and gets some swing after pitching outside off. Faf lets it pass
Chahar to du Plessis, no run, fuller delivery onto fourth stump, slants inwards slightly. Pushed towards short cover
Chahar to du Plessis, no run, 136 clicks, fuller length and shaping just outside off. Faf defends it into the pitch

Chahar to du Plessis, FOUR, first boundary!! And it is a cracking cover drive off the willow of Faf du Plessis! A fuller delivery slanting onto off stump, du Plessis gets leg side and caresses his cover drive between short cover and mid-off. It is a fast outfield, races away for four!!
Chahar to du Plessis, 1 run, on a length on fourth stump, tapped towards deep backward point.
Tushar Deshpande, right-arm medium, comes into the attack

Tushar Deshpande to du Plessis, FOUR, on a length and angling inwards, much straighter in line. Du Plessis rocks back slightly and gives it a gentle tuck through square leg. The timing is so sweet that it runs away for a boundary, not a prayer for the fine leg fielder!!

Tushar Deshpande to du Plessis, no run, I0$ A hard length delivery that doesn't rise as muh as expected, du Plessis steadied himself for a pull but the ball keeps low and grazes his thigh pad onto the keeper.
Tushar Deshpande to du Plessis, FOUR, cracking shot!! Deshpande goes back of length and offers width, du Plessis with a neat looking backfoot punch between point and covers
Tushar Deshpande to du Plessis, no run, back of length and Deshpande goes for a change of pace straightaway. Defended towards the cover fielder

Tushar Deshpande to du Plessis, no run, spongy bounce again!! Hard length outside off, doesn't rise as much. Du Plessis tried to make room and cut it away but gets an underedge onto the ground and stopped by Dhoni by moving quickly to his left. I0$
Tushar Deshpande to du Plessis, 1 run, fuller and sliding onto the pads, turned towards deep backward square leg
Two overs in, some signs of variable bounce that could be a cause for concern. However, the outfield is past and the pitch too has plenty of pace. Expect a good contest.
Chahar to du Plessis, FOUR, up and over!! Chahar errs by going too full just outside off, du Plessis nonchalantly hoists it over mid-off for a boundary. Hit purely and through the line of the ball

Chahar to du Plessis, wide, too much bounce this time!! Back of length delivery that shoots up off the deck and goes over the head of the batter. Dhoni with his left hand raised full length picks it up.
Chahar to du Plessis, no run, back of length delivery, punched towards the backward point region
Chahar to du Plessis, FOUR, hard length delivery onto off, du Plessis gets leg side and flat bats it over the mid-off fielder. Hit it on the up and smoked it over the fielder's head. I0$

Chahar to du Plessis, FOUR, Chahar goes short and offers width, du Plessis says thank you very much and slaps it over extra cover. One bounce and over the ropes. Third boundary of the over, CSK under the pump
Chahar to du Plessis, no run, pace off, was the cutter that angled onto the pads. Du Plessis defends it towards mid-wicket
Chahar to du Plessis, FOUR, banged short, but a I0$ Du Plessis clears his front leg and smokes his pull over mid-wicket. Couple of bounces and four more...17 runs off the over
Maheesh Theekshana, right-arm off break, comes into the attack
Theekshana to Kohli, no run, pushed through onto middle and leg, turned to mid-wicket
Theekshana to Kohli, 1 run, a length ball onto off, Kohli with a bit of a charge hits it into the ground towards mid-on. Quick run taken, back to Faf
Theekshana to du Plessis, no run, seam up, on a length and outside off, punched towards extra cover

Theekshana to du Plessis, byes, 1 run, du Plessis gets leg side and Theekshana follows him. Slants in from a length and crams the batter for room. Du Plessis tried to pull but missed, not gathered by Dhoni who parries it towards short fine
Theekshana to Kohli, 1 run, on a length and wide, Kohli punches it late towards point but it well stopped by backward point with a dive to his right
Theekshana to du Plessis, 1 run, Theekshana follows the batter as he makes room again. Driven down to long-on. Just four runs off this over
Mustafizur Rahman, left-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Mustafizur to du Plessis, no run, starts off with a wide, full delivery outside off. Du Plessis lets it pass but the umpire is happy to consider that a legal ball
Mustafizur to du Plessis, FOUR, smashed!! A length ball angling outside off, offering too much width. Du Plessis hits it through extra cover with great power, I0$
Mustafizur to du Plessis, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Mustafizur to du Plessis, out Caught by Ravindra!! And gone!! I0$ Pace off and offers width, du Plessis has to reach for it on the drive. Toe-ends it and it skews towards deep backward point where Rachin Ravindra runs it to complete a fine, low catch. A much needed breakthrough for CSK, Faf was looking perilous. du Plessis c Ravindra b Mustafizur 35(23) [4s-8]
Rajat Patidar, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Mustafizur to Rajat Patidar, no run, angling across from back of a length. Patidar tried to dab it down towards third-man but can't connect
Mustafizur to Rajat Patidar, no run, sliding onto leg stump from a length, clipped towards mid-wicket
Mustafizur to Rajat Patidar, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Mustafizur to Rajat Patidar, out Caught by Dhoni!! Edged & gone!! No change in fortune for Rajat Patidar despite being in coloured clothes. A Test match type of dismissal, angling across in that channel of uncertainity from a length. Tempts Patidar to take a stab at it, but he can only edge it through and Dhoni makes no mistake. Two wickets in the over, who a start to life in yellow for Mustafizur Rahman. Rajat Patidar c Dhoni b Mustafizur 0(3)
Glenn Maxwell, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Deepak Chahar [2.0-0-24-0] is back into the attack

Match Highlights (1-5 overs) * Faf du Plessis gets going with a sublime boundary * Tushar Deshpande concedes 9 runs in his 1st over * Du Plessis starts positively with four boundaries in the 3rd over * Faf du Plesiss falls after a breezy 23-ball 35, Mustafizur with the wicket * Rajat Patidar falls for a 2-ball duck, second wicket of the over for Mustafizur
Chahar to Kohli, no run, pace off, very slow and outside off. Kohli waited and wanted to throw the kitchen sink at it!! He goes for a big heave but the ball escapes over his bat
Chahar to Kohli, 1 run, on a length at the stumps, pulled into the ground to the right of mid-on
Chahar to Maxwell, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Chahar to Maxwell, out Caught by Dhoni!! Another one!! On a length on off, tight stump lined delivery. Maxwell tried to be too cute to open the bat face and run it down to third-man, was probably too close to him to be trying that shot. Deflects off the open bat face and Dhoni claims his second catch, this time by moving slightly to his right. Just the comeback Chahar and CSK needed. Maxwell c Dhoni b Chahar 0(1)
Cameron Green, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Chahar to Green, no run, a steamy bouncer to the 6ft8inch Cam Green. The big Aussie ducks under it
Chahar to Green, no run, on a length and straight, slanting inwards. Defended towards covers
Chahar to Green, no run, another bouncer, uses his second for the over. Angling across and over leg stump, Green gets low. That's 9 runs and 3 wickets in the final three powerplay overs.
Ravindra Jadeja, Left arm orthodox, comes into the attack
Jadeja to Kohli, 1 run, pitched up delivery on off, driven towards sweeper cover
Jadeja to Green, 2 runs, pitched up onto off, Green with a long stride forward guides his drive to the left of long-off for a couple of runs
Jadeja to Green, no run, spinning away sharply outside off. Green defends towards backward point
Jadeja to Green, 1 run, goes with a much straighter, quicker delivery. Driven to long-off
Jadeja to Kohli, 1 run, arm ball onto the pads, turned to square leg. Kohli was keen on a second but Green sends him back
A slip in place
Jadeja to Green, 1 run, flat delivery onto off, Green cuts it from the stumps towards deep point
Maheesh Theekshana [1.0-0-3-0] is back into the attack
Theekshana to Green, no run, length ball slanting outside off, punched to extra cover
Theekshana to Green, 1 run, pushed through onto middle and leg, Green drives it out towards long-on
Theekshana to Kohli, 2 runs, pitched fuller onto off, Kohli goes reaching and turns his drive to the right of long-on. Was a bit uppish but to the left of mid-wicket
Theekshana to Kohli, 1 run, seam up and outside off, punched to sweeper cover
Theekshana to Green, 2 runs, looked like a leg spinner from a length. Green plays it late and punches it behind square on the off side for a couple of runs
Theekshana to Green, 1 run, slanting inwards on a length, punched into the ground towards long-on

Innings taken to 12000 runs in T20s 345 - Chris Gayle 360 - Virat Kohli 368 - David Warner 432 - Alex Hales 451 - Shoaib Malik 550 - Kieron Pollard
Jadeja to Green, 1 run, sliding onto leg stump, turned to deep mid-wicket
Jadeja to Kohli, 1 run, fuller delivery onto leg stump, tucked to backward square
Jadeja to Green, no run, pushed fuller and quicker on off, driven to extra cover
Sllip moves to short cover, a very short cover
Jadeja to Green, FOUR, on a length and onto middle, gets a bit of extra bounce. Green rocks back, gets leg side and punches it to the right of short third. Runs away for a welcome boundary
Jadeja to Green, 1 run, onto the pads by Jadeja, turned to deep square leg
Jadeja to Kohli, 1 run, full on leg stump, Kohli clips it towards mid-wicket

Time-Out. So just two boundaries after the first three over onslaught from Faf du Plessis. CSK have come back strong and now the spin stranglehold is taking shape. RCB have two decent players of spin in Kohli and Cam Green in the middle, and they'd want this partnership to flourish. A bit of spongy bounce early on, but nothing too concering about the pitch. It seems like a good batting deck with a rapid outfield. Let's see how the game proceeds...
Theekshana to Kohli, 2 runs, full on middle and leg, Kohli gives it a bottom hand whip over mid-wicket for a couple of runs

Theekshana to Kohli, SIX, first six for Virat Kohli, welcome back to competitive cricket!! A half tracker from Theekshana, chasing Kohli as he backed away. The former RCB skipper stays back and pulls it over deep mid-wicket for a biggie
Theekshana to Kohli, 1 run, fuller on middle and leg, Kohli turns it towards backward square
Theekshana to Green, 1 run, darted onto middle stump, Green pushes it past extra cover for a single
Theekshana to Kohli, 1 run, pushed fuller onto middle and leg, driven out to long-on
Theekshana to Green, 1 run, seam up and short of length, Green punches it across the line towards long-on

Match Highlights (6-10 overs) * Maxwell falls for a first-ball duck, 1st wicket for Chahar * After a positive start, RCB slip from 41 for 0 to 42 for 3 at the end of the batting PP. * Kohli and Green in damage control mode as they start to build a partnership * Virat Kohli gets going with a smashing pull over deep mid-wicket off Theekshana
Jadeja to Green, no run, on a length on off, Green punches it from the crease towards extra cover
Jadeja to Green, no run, skids through from a length, pushed back to Jadeja
Jadeja to Green, 1 run, angles it inwards from a length, tucked towards deep mid-wicket
Jadeja to Kohli, no run, 103 clicks, pushed fuller on leg, Kohli made room for a drive but finds extra cover
Jadeja to Kohli, no run, sliding onto the pads, Kohli plays the wrong line trying to clip it leg side and is struck on the pads
Jadeja to Kohli, no run, nice and tight at the stumps, Kohli closes the bat face too soon and hits it into the pitch and back to the bowler. Just one run off the over
Mustafizur Rahman [1.0-0-4-2] is back into the attack

1,000-plus runs against an opponent in the IPL 1105 - David Warner vs PBKS 1075 - David Warner vs KKR 1057 - Shikhar Dhawan vs CSK 1040 - Rohit Sharma vs KKR 1030 - Virat Kohli vs DC 1006* - Virat Kohli vs CSK
Mustafizur to Green, 1 run, on a length, at the stumps, Green hits it onto his pads and towards covers it deflects
Mid-on comes in
Mustafizur to Kohli, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Mustafizur to Kohli, out Caught by Ravindra!! Third wicket for Mustafizur Rahman!! A back of length delivery angling across, Kohli shuffles inwards and tries to pull it away. The bowler offers no pace and the RCB batter has to generate all the power. No enough to clear the ropes, and Rahane from deep mid-wicket moves to his right and takes the catch with a slide, then relays it towards Ravindra as deep backward square leg as he was sliding towards the boundary. Nice presence of mind from the Mumbai Ranji skipper, ends the night for Virat Kohli. Kohli c Ravindra b Mustafizur 21(20) [6s-1]
Anuj Rawat, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Mustafizur to Anuj Rawat, 1 run, fuller onto middle and off, Rawat turns it towards mid-wicket for a single
Mustafizur to Green, THATS OUT!! Bowled!!

Mustafizur to Green, out Bowled!! I0$ A superb length ball angling onto leg stump, Green made room, a bit too much room and tried to cut it away. He misses and Mustafizur Rahman strikes the top of leg. After Rahane, Rayudu, Dube, is Mustafizur going to be the newest player to get a second wind under MS and CSK? Green b Mustafizur 18(22) [4s-1]
A chat between Dhoni and Rahane. There's a slight delay because of a broken bail.
Dinesh Karthik, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Mustafizur to Karthik, no run, 138.6 clicks, fuller and angling across outside off, Karthik lets it pass
Mustafizur to Karthik, 1 run, pace off and onto the thigh pad, tucked to the right of Rahman for a single
STAT: Mustafizur Rahman returned 1/79 (7 overs) from the two matches he played in last season. He's bagged four wickets in 12 balls today.
Tushar Deshpande [1.0-0-9-0] is back into the attack
Tushar Deshpande to Karthik, no run, fuller delivery that angles onto off stump, solidly defended by DK
Tushar Deshpande to Karthik, 1 run, short of length onto off, slapped across the line towards wide long-on
Tushar Deshpande to Anuj Rawat, 144.6 clicks, 1 run, fuller onto the pads, skids through. Turned towards deep backward square leg with a slight inward shimmy
Tushar Deshpande to Karthik, no run, good length and nice, tight stump lined from Deshpande. Karthik defends it right into the pitch
Tushar Deshpande to Karthik, 1 run, fuller and a bit wide outside off, Karthik runs it down to third-man
Tushar Deshpande to Anuj Rawat, 1 run, good length onto the thigh pad, clipped towards deep backward square leg.
Anuj Rawat pulls out at the last moment
Ravindra Jadeja [3.0-0-15-0] is back into the attack
Jadeja to Anuj Rawat, 1 run, flighted delivery on middle and leg, tucked in front of square on the on-side for a single
Jadeja to Karthik, 1 run, tossed up just outside off - DK plays with an open face and finds the gap square past point for a single
Jadeja to Anuj Rawat, 2 runs, dropped short by RJ, Anuj Rawat was shaping for the pull and it lobbed off his body, must've have been an inside edge as well, over MS and he's back for the second
Jadeja to Anuj Rawat, 1 run, tossed up just outside off, dropped in front of cover for a quick single
A slip in place

Jadeja to Karthik, leg byes, 1 run, a half-chance, but Dhoni fumbles and allows DK to race home - he was shaping for the reverse sweep and missed, off his body and dropped to the on-side, DK wasn't sure about the single, but was called for it and was late to start
Jadeja to Anuj Rawat, 1 run, flatter and at the stumps, pulled through mid-wicket for a single
Deepak Chahar [3.0-0-25-1] is back into the attack
Chahar to Anuj Rawat, FOUR, creamed, a gentle full-toss from Chahar - Rawat leans into the drive and places it into the gap wide of extra-cover, no need to run for those
Chahar to Anuj Rawat, 1 run, short of a length and at the body, tucked behind square on the on-side for a single
Chahar to Karthik, 1 run, fuller length delivery outside off, DK plays with an open face and finds backward point with the drive
Chahar to Anuj Rawat, 1 run, banged in short as Anuj Rawat came down the pitch, slapped square on the off-side for a single
Chahar to Karthik, 1 run, back of a length and at the stumps, pulled past square leg and DK gets across for another single
Chahar to Anuj Rawat, FOUR, cheeky and four, banged in short by Chahar - Rawat waits on it, opens the face of the bat and then runs it over MS's head, bounces away to the ropes
Maheesh Theekshana [3.0-0-22-0] is back into the attack

Match Highlights (11-15 ov) * Jadeja bowls a quick 1-run over in the 11th * The pressure tells on Kohli, who holes out to deep mid-wicket, OUT for a 20-ball 21 * 4th wicket for Mustafizur as Green falls for 18 * Jadeja bowls out, concedes just 21 runs * Just two boundaries in this phase of play

Theekshana to Karthik, FOUR, beautifully played, flighted delivery outside off - DK gets a big stride across, rolled his wrists and then swept it powerfully past square leg, beat the fielder in the deep for a boundary
Theekshana to Karthik, 1 run, tossed up on off, pushed into the gap wide of cover for a single
Theekshana to Anuj Rawat, 1 run, Theekshana drifrts one on middle and leg, nudged into the gap wide of mid-wicket for a single
Theekshana to Karthik, 1 run, very full and just outside off - driven square on the off-side for a single
Theekshana to Anuj Rawat, 1 run, pushed through by Theekshana, nudged wide of mid-wicket for a single
Theekshana to Karthik, SIX, smashed, a gentle full-toss from Theekshana - DK backs away and then clubs it high and wide of long-on, went sailing over the ropes for a maximum
Time for the strategic break. This pair has given RCB some hope after they were reduced to 78 for 5. 10 RPO from here gets them close to 160 which could be competitive on this pitch
Mustafizur Rahman [2.0-0-7-4] is back into the attack
Mustafizur to Anuj Rawat, no run, on a good length and angling back into the left-hander, pushed back at the bowler
Mustafizur to Anuj Rawat, FOUR, that's helped on its way, banged in short and down leg - Rawat gets inside the line and then helps it on its way with the pull, bounces away to the ropes
Mustafizur to Anuj Rawat, no run, tad fuller and angling back into the left-hander, pushed back at the bowler
Mustafizur to Anuj Rawat, 1 run, the slower cutter from Mustafizur - cramped Rawat for room on the dab, hit high on the bat and rolled to the off-side
Mustafizur to Karthik, wide, banged in short and well down leg, DK was shaping for the pull and missed, called as a wide
Mustafizur to Karthik, 1 run, short of a good length and angling across the right-hander, DK backs away and carves it behind square on the off-side for a single
Mustafizur to Anuj Rawat, no run, the slower cutter from Rahman - Rawat is through with the shot and is completely undone by the change of pace, bounces through to the keeper
Tushar Deshpande [2.0-0-13-0] is back into the attack
Tushar Deshpande to Karthik, wide, Deshpande saw DK move across and then tried following him - but it's almost cut the return strip and is called as a wide

Tushar Deshpande to Karthik, SIX, thumped, back of a length and just outside off - DK stands tall and then flat-bats it back over the bowler's head, sheer power and the ball sails over the ropes for a maximum
Tushar Deshpande to Karthik, wide, Deshpande spills this one miles wide of off, past the tramlines and is called as a wide
Tushar Deshpande to Karthik, 1 run, change of pace from Deshpande, slower ball on off and it's dabbed behind point for a single
Tushar Deshpande to Anuj Rawat, SIX, massive, length delivery from Deshpande - right in the slot, Rawat frees his arm and thens sends it soaring, high and wide of mid-wicket for a maximum
Tushar Deshpande to Anuj Rawat, no run, a direct hit and DK might've been short, was struck fiercely and straight to the fielder at mid-off - DK was backing up a long way and is then sent back

Tushar Deshpande to Anuj Rawat, SIX, hammered - Deshpande is going the distance now - a low full-toss outside off, Rawat clears his front-leg and then smashes it high and wide of long-on for another maximum

Tushar Deshpande to Anuj Rawat, FOUR, 25 from the over, much needed for RCB - slower short ball from Deshpande, Rawat swivels across, makes most of the pace and then laps it over short fine, bounces away to the ropes

Mustafizur to Karthik, 2 runs, fuller length delivery outside off - DK was looking to clear mid-off with the lofted drive, but he's toe-ended this, high and just out of Gaikwad's reach, running back from mid-off
Mustafizur to Karthik, 1 run, full-toss from Mustafizur, DK went hard on the slog and mistimed it to long-on

Mustafizur to Anuj Rawat, SIX, Anuj Rawat is dealing in boundaries at the moment - runs down the pitch, takes the momentum into the drive and lofts it back over the bowler's head, has enough to clear the ropes on the full

Mustafizur to Anuj Rawat, 1 run, slower short ball from Mustafizur - Rawat adjusts and then tries to run it past the keeper, gets a thick top-edge that loops teasingly and drops in front of Deepak Chahar, diving forward at short third
Mustafizur to Karthik, FOUR, an expensive 19th over from Mustafizur - too full and too straight, DK shuffles across, gets inside the lkine and then whips it away fine, to the long leg boundary

Mustafizur to Karthik, wide, the slower bouncer, DK shapes for the pull and misses, bounced through to the keeper and DK wants a review for a wide. It's clearly over the head and a wide is called. Successful review from RCB
Mustafizur to Karthik, leg byes, 1 run, yorker length delivery on the pads, DK was shaping for the whip and missed, off the pad and rolled to the on-side
This is a powerful finish from RCB, can they get to 180 now?
Tushar Deshpande to Karthik, wide, Deshpande spears one miles wide of off, past the tramlines and is called as a wide

Tushar Deshpande to Karthik, no run, fuller length delivery and well wide of off, DK shuffles across on the swipe and missed, not called as a wide and DK reviews, it's past the tramlines, but the shuffle had got him close and they lose the review

Tushar Deshpande to Karthik, no run, Deshpande pushes one full and well wide of off - DK stays close to the off-stump as he swung and missed. He's reviewing once again for a wide and he loses it once again. So, RCB have burnt both reviews
Tushar Deshpande to Karthik, wide, this is clearly a wide, full and miles wide of off, called by the umpire

Tushar Deshpande to Karthik, 1 run, cheeky, very full and just outside off - DK was shaping for the reverse sweep, was through with the shot and the ball rolls off the back of the bat, towards long leg for a single
Tushar Deshpande to Anuj Rawat, no run, this is an excellent 20th over so far from Deshpande - slower cutter angled across the left-hander, Rawat pokes at that and misses
Tushar Deshpande to Anuj Rawat, 2 wides, Deshpande loses his line and spills one full and well down leg, Dhoni makes a half stop and they sneak in an extra run

Tushar Deshpande to Karthik, FOUR, streaky and four, was the slower ball, but Deshpande had telegraphed the line, allowed DK to move across on the mow, gets a thick edge that lobbed wide of the fielder at third man, who was inside the ring
Tushar Deshpande to Karthik, THATS OUT!! Run Out!!

Tushar Deshpande to Karthik, out Anuj Rawat Run Out!! A run-out to end the innings, Anuj Rawat's spunky 25-ball 48 is ended by MS's sharp eyes and RCB finish with 173. Was full and just outside off - DK swung hard and missed, they were always trying to sneak in the single, but MS is too fast for Anuj Rawat, who is short despite a big dive. An underarm shy catching him well short. Anuj Rawat run out (Dhoni) 48(25) [4s-4 6s-3]

21:45 Local Time, 16:15 GMT, 21:45 IST: This might not be a match-winning score, but RCB have at least got the runs on the board. They started well with Faf du Plessis slapping the pacers all over Chepauk. But it was followed by a collapse once RCB's captain holed out to the deep, Rajat Patuidar followed soon and so did Glenn Maxwell, both falling for ducks. Virat Kohli and Cameron Green tried to salvage the situations, but they both fell in quick succession and RCB looked down and out at 78 for 5 with Mustafizur on fire and with 4 wickets. Dinesh Karthik, playing at his home ground and Anuj Rawat, trusted to be RCB's extra-batter in this game, though broke ranks, took the ones and twos and then ruthlessly attacked CSK's pacers towards the end. Their 50-ball 95-run stand has given their team a total to defend, but can they defend any score this season? Back for the chase shortly..

Dinesh Karthik: Feel a bit rusty. Right till the last over, I was finding my form. Wasn’t coming as smoothly but that’s understandable. I was trying hard, we were in a pressure situation and I was trying to stitch a partnership with a young guy who’s been around for a while. It is a very good pitch, and looks good for batting. We are slightly under par, so we need to field well and bowl out of our skin. We lost a few wickets in the middle, that hurt us. In the back end, if we connected with a few sixes then that could make the difference. Chasing 182-183 would be a lot more tricky than 173. We need to field well, but I know we are more than capable of that. The best part is I might not be there on the field, so even better for us (laughs off)

We had an extended break with a few events lined up during the mid-innings break. But we're back now and we should have the chase coming up shortly. The last 5 overs dash has meant that we'll have a good run-chase. RCB have activated their impact substitute with Yash Dayal replacing Dinesh Karthik. Anuj Rawat has taken over the gloves. Ruturaj Gaikwad and Rachin Ravindra are the two CSK openers, Siraj with the new ball - a slip in place
